Create a css file in our project
mysite/static/css/ --create static,css
mysite/statis/images --create images

create style.css under css folder
body {
    background-color:blue;
}

link this file inside the home.html

also using img tag add the image to home.html

it is not loading anything still

Special config to serve the static files
Goto settings.py
go to static url

# Static files (CSS, JavaScript, Images)
# https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/5.2/howto/static-files/

STATIC_URL = 'static/'
STATIC_ROOT = BASE_DIR /'static/'
STATICFILES_DIRS = [
    'mysite/static'
]

go to home.html
ontop of file, load the static
{% load static %}

in home.html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/style.css' %}">


STATIC_ROOT
collect static collects all the static files inthe static folder which is inside the mysite folder-- for deplpyment purpose-- used after the site has been depl on the server

STATICFILES_DIR
list of folders where django will search for additional static files when yo urun python manage.py runserver command
